  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Filterable<T>
    Abstracts the fetch method, used by filtered query objects to fetch the results.

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Firestorm
    The main class of the Firestorm API, which allows basic interactions with the Firestore.
    FirestormBatch
    Enables Firestore batch writes.
    FirestormConfig
    Stores Firestore configuration - enables quick parsing of service account files.
    FirestormEventListener<T>
    Implements logic for Firestore update events.
    FirestormFilterable<T>
    An object that enables quick use of Firestore filters without using additional DocumentReferences.
    FirestormObject
    Abstracts an object which will be stored in Firestore.
    FirestormOperation
    Abstracts a Firestorm operation, its execution and callbacks.
    FirestormTransaction
    Enables Firestore transactions.
    Paginator<T>
    Enables easy pagination.
    QueryResult<T>
    Models a result returned from a query.
    TransactionFilterable<T>
    A filterable used in transactions.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    FirestormException
    Exception thrown by Firestorm.
    TooManyOperationsException
    An exception thrown by setting too many batch operations (over 500).
    TransactionException
    An exception thrown during a transaction.
